Description: Fragment of handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora, gradual curve. Clay fine buff-brown. Rectangular stamp with Greek inscription.
Production date: 213 BC (see N. Badoud, Le temps de Rhodes (2015) 142.)
Curator's comments: Name Charmokles. Trimmed. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0246.24.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0649)
